Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Slice the @baking potato{1} into 1cm thick rounds (no need to peel). Peel and
grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the
@echalion shallot{} into small pieces.

Once boiling, add the potato slices to the water and simmer until you can easily
slip a knife through, ~{8-12%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When the
oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{120%g} and shallot.

Stir-fry until the mince is browned and the shallot is softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any
excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the beef cooks, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1} in a #sieve{}.

Add the garlic to the mince and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1}, mixed beans, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g},
@red wine stock paste{28%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.
Roughly crush half the beans in the pan with the back of a #fork{} or
#potato masher{}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until
thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Remove from the heat, then taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the beef simmers, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{45%g}. Halve any
thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Spoon the beef into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} when ready, then
layer the cooked potato slices over the top.

Sprinkle over the cheese, then grill until golden and bubbling,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wipe out the mince frying pan and pop it back on medium-high heat
with a drizzle of @oil{}.

When hot, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes},
then add a splash of @water{}.

Pop a lid on the pan, or cover in #foil{}, and cook until tender,
~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the hotpot is ready, allow to stand for ~{2%minutes}, then serve with the
Tenderstem® broccoli alongside. Enjoy!